  "rationale": "v4 keeps v3's atomic-feature design (each feature = exactly one attribute delta vs fixed baseline; 20 examples per feature, 9 features x 20 = 180 images) and replaces the style register after the user vetoed v3's output for the Trellis image-to-3D pipeline: 'anime eyes / mouth don't work very well with trellis. try more realistically shaded, but not full humanoid. we need realistic eyeballs.'",
  "v4_style_selection": "Chosen by a 9-variant prompt-probe study (probes/style_v4/, 36 images, seeds 1-4 each). Findings: 'painterly' is ignored by z-image-turbo; 'realistic/photorealistic eyes' either has no effect in a 3D-render register or flips the whole image to photoreal cosplay (vetoed as 'full humanoid'); 'figurine' + eye emphasis collapses to chibi nendoroid (v1 veto); '3D VRChat avatar render' pulls a fox-muzzle face on ~half of seeds. Winner probe_i (4/4 human face, single tail, full body, adult proportions, dimensional 3D eyes): '3D anime avatar render, beautiful human woman face, soft semi-realistic shading, dimensional glossy eyes with detailed iris and catchlights, tall adult proportions'.",
  "single_tail_note": "cfg=1 (turbo) makes the negative prompt mathematically inert, which is why v2's negative-prompt tail fix never worked. The single-tail constraint is now positive-prompt ('exactly one single fluffy fox tail behind her'); in probes it held 24/28 vs frequent two-tail splays in v3.",
